<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-07T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1180.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Cairo</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AO1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-07T19:00:00+02:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11:58 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>General commanding British Egypt issued to-day proclamation in the name
                            of <persName corresp="#p_GV1">King George</persName> assuming sole
                            burden of defending Egypt against Turkey, claiming violation Egyptian
                            frontier and agreeing not to ask Mohammedan Egyptians’ assistance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_AO1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>